      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I AM BRAVE (4) slow into stride on resumption and returned excellent closing splits for a respectable sixth over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Key jockey change and she should get the right speed from the wide gate. Hard to hold out. GAELIC GEM (6) blinkers go on third-up and will find this more to her liking after disappointing behind Escargoes over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Lone win came at this trip and no surprise to see her in the finish today. IRON FURY (1) is experiencing a long win drought and gets another chance third-up over the 1200m. Given the gun run from the gate but failed to close off when fourth over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Placed twice at this course and stays in the mix. LUMA LIGHT (3) progressive filly resuming from a lengthy spell. Fitted with the two trials and should handle the conditions with the 3kg claimer aboard.",
